Claims Claims 1. Computer-implemented method for training a machine learning system (8) to denoise a provided input signal (S), wherein training the machine learning system (8) comprises the steps of: â¢ Providing a first input signal (1) and a first value (2) to a first part (4) of the machine learning system (8), wherein the first input signal (1) characterizes a noisy signal and the first value (2) characterizes a randomly drawn value; â¢ Determining, by the first part (4), a first output signal (9) for the first input signal (1) and the first value (2); â¢ Determining, by a second part (5) of the machine learning system (8), a second value (6) based on the first output signal (9), wherein the second value (6) characterizes a probability of the first output signal (9) to characterize a noisy signal; â¢ Determining, by the second part (5), a third value (7) based on a supplied second input signal (3), wherein the second input signal (3) characterizes a non-noisy signal and wherein the third value (7) characterizes a probability of the second input signal (3) to characterize a non-noisy signal; â¢ Training the machine learning system (8), wherein training comprises: o Adapting a plurality of parameters of the first part (4) according to a gradient of the second value (6) with respect to the plurality of parameters of the first part (4); o Adapting a plurality of parameters of the second part (5) according to a gradient of a sum of the second value (6) and the third value (7) with respect to the plurality of parameters of the second part (5). 2. Method according to claim 1, wherein the method further comprises the steps of: â¢ Providing a third input signal and a fourth value to the first part (4), wherein the third input signal characterizes a non-noisy signal; 

 â¢ Determining, by the first part (4), a second output signal for the third input signal and the fourth value; â¢ Adapting a plurality of parameters of the first part (4) according to a deviation of the second output signal to the third input signal. 3. Method according to claim 1 or 2, wherein the method further comprises the steps of: â¢ Determining, by the first part (4) and based on the first input signal (1) and the first value (2), a fifth value characterizing a classification of the type of noise characterized by the first input signal (1); â¢ Adapting a plurality of parameters of the first part (4) according to a deviation of a class characterized by the fifth value and a class of noise type corresponding to the first input signal (1). 4. Method according to claim 2, wherein the method further comprises the steps of: â¢ Determining, by the first part (4) and based on the third input signal and the fourth value, a fifth value characterizing a classification of the type of noise characterized by the third input signal; â¢ Adapting a plurality of parameters of the first part according to a deviation of a class characterized by the fifth value and a class characterizing an absence of noise. 5. Method according to any one of the claims 2 to 4, wherein the deviation of the second output signal to the third input signal is characterized by the formula wherein Â® is the third input signal and G is the first part. 6. Computer-implemented method for determining a denoised signal (x) from an input signal (S) comprising the steps of: â¢ Providing a first part (4) according to any one of the claims 1 to 5; â¢ Determining an input signal (x) by the first part (4) based on the input signal (S) and a randomly-drawn first value (2); 

 â¢ Providing the output signal as denoised signal (x). 7. Method according to claim 6, wherein providing the first part (4) comprises training the first part (4) according to any one of the claims 1 to 5. 8. Method according to claim 6 or 7, wherein the denoised signal (x) is used as input of a control system (40), wherein the control system (40) is configured to determine a control signal (A) of an actuator (10) based on the denoised signal (x). 9. Method according to claim 6 or 7, wherein the denoised signal (x) is used as input to a virtual sensor (30) for determining a property of the input signal (S) that is not measured by the input signal (S) itself. 10. Method according to any one of the previous claims wherein first input signal and/or second input signal and/or third input signal and/or input signal (S) are sensor signals. 11. Training system (140), which is configured to carry out the training method according to any one of the claims 1 to 5. 12. Computer program that is configured to cause a computer to carry out the method according to any one of the claims 1 to 9 with all of its steps if the computer program is carried out by a processor (45, 145). 13. Machine-readable storage medium (46, 146) on which the computer program according to claim 11 is stored.
